               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184208220204"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18420822-name-1539" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1539" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1539" type="surname" value="MALLETT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18420822-name-1539" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>JOSEPH MALLETT</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a congreve-match manufacturer—the prisoner was my porter. About ten o'clock in the morning of the 13th of <hi rend="italic">August</hi>, I sent him out—after he was gone I had something told me, and I went <hi rend="italic">to</hi> the place in my factory where I kept my money—I missed one of two five-shilling packets of halfpence, which were safe about five minutes before—I followed him, and said, "If you will give me back the five-shill lings-worth of halfpence, nobody shall know anything about it"—he said he had got nothing—I told him to go back to the factory, to justify him<lb></lb>self—I saw him go to the factory—he came back again, and said he had cleared himself with my partner, and would go <hi rend="italic">on</hi> with my goods—I said, "Have you found the five shillings?"—he said, "It is not found"—I followed him with my eye to a little house, before you arrive at the factory—I saw him put his hand into his pocket—then he came back to me—I said I would not let him go with my goods—he left my goods, and went away—he came back on Monday morning—I have since seen the packet of copper.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Why did not you put a stop to this, by searching him at the time? <hi rend="italic">A. I</hi> did not know I was allowed—he has never been searched—the officer took him on the Tuesday—he came for his wages on the Monday—I did not pay him—he came again on Tuesday for his wages—I did not pay him—I owed him 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 9<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he had 7<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. a week—no victuals or clothes—he used to work from six o'clock in the morning to seven at night.</p>
